FBIS4-46167 "jptot022__l94076" JPRS-TOT-94-022-L JPRS Terrorism FOUO 27 May 1994 CENTRAL EURASIA RUSSIA `Terrorists' Seize 30 Hostages on Board Bus in North Caucasus `Terrorists' Seize 30 Hostages on Board Bus in North Caucasus Kidnappers' Demands To Be Met LD2705061594 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0500 GMT 27 May 94 LD2705061594 Moscow Radio Rossii Network Russian BFN [Text] [Announcer] Our correspondent Valeriy Kuts is at Mineralnyye Vody airport where the hostage-release operation is under way. He has just filed the following report: [Kuts] By this hour, the representatives of the Federal Counterintelligence Service and of the Russian Interior Ministry have handed $8 million over to the terrorists who are staying in the bus parked at the Mineralnyye Vody airport number two. The bandits are still keeping hostage three women and two men, one of whom is the driver. The helicopter with sufficient fuel and without a crew will be given to them very soon. The position of the hostage-release operation headquarters is quite clear: All demands of the terrorists should be carried out and will be carried out.
